.TH "pcim_iomap" 9 "pcim_iomap" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcim_iomap \- Managed pcim_iomap()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void __iomem *" pcim_iomap
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "int bar "  ","
.BI "unsigned long maxlen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
PCI device to iomap for
.IP "bar" 12
BAR to iomap
.IP "maxlen" 12
Maximum length of iomap
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Managed \fBpci_iomap\fP.  Map is automatically unmapped on driver
detach.
